<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04444</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT STRENGTHENING WORKERS RIGHT TO SECURITY OF TENURE, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE ARTICLES 106 TO 109 OF BOOK III, ARTICLES 294 [279] TO 296 [281] OF BOOK VI, AND ARTICLE 303 [288] OF BOOK VII OF PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 442, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE LABOR CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES, AS AMENDED</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to totally prohibit the practice of contracting, subcontracting, manpower agency hiring, outsourcing, including those undertaken by so-called service cooperatives engaged in manpower supply thereby strengthening security of tenure and ending its abusive practices.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>MENDOZA, RAYMUND DEMOCRITO C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-11-16</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB06908</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2016-11-23</td></tr></table>